Name: Western Meadowlark
Description: Medium-sized bird with a yellow breast, dark V on breast, intricate pattern above, complex and beautiful song

Name: Cinnamon Teal
Description: Deep red male, blue wing patches

Name: Northern Shoveler
Description: Colorful duck with green head, huge shovel bill, yellow eye

Name: Gadwall
Description: Gray duck with white wing patch, pretty common, loud calls

Name: American Wigeon
Description: Brown-gray duck with green crescent on head, light forehead

Name: Mallard
Description: The Duck

Name: Green-winged Teal
Description: Small duck with brown head, green crescent, white spur on gray body

Name: Canvasback
Description: Common in winter, white back and body, red head, forehead more sloped than Redhead

Name: Redhead
Description: Normal shaped duck with a reddish head, gray back, black breast, forehead steeper than Canvasback, pretty hard to see in Bay Area

Name: Surf Scoter
Description: Huge "nostrils", wacky bright bill in the winter but dark brown plumage in summer

Name: Common Goldeneye
Description: Male is white with dark back and greenish head, sloped head, female is brown and nondescript

Name: Hooded Merganser
Description: Has a large black and white crest it can raise and lower, brown and white body, fart-like calls

Name: Ruddy Duck
Description: Small duck with pin-tail, dark cap and white face, gets a cool blue bill and ruddy color, but in summer

Name: Pied-billed Grebe
Description: Common at freshwater ponds, brown with a triangular gray bill, sometimes with a black ring around it

Name: Eared Grebe
Description: Small grebe, dark on top and light on the bottom, cool head plumes in summer but we see it in winter :(

Name: Western Grebe
Description: Black on top and white on bottom, black over eye, upturned dusky yellow bill

Name: Black-necked Stilt
Description: Almost always found at the marsh, super long pink/red legs and black and white body

Name: American Avocet
Description: Avocados, upturned bill, black and white in winter but has some orange in the summer

Name: Long-billed Curlew
Description: Very large shorebird, very long downturned bill

Name: Marbled Godwit
Description: Large shorebird with slightly upturned, bicolored pink/gray bill, cinnamon color

Name: Least Sandpiper
Description: Tiny peep with yellow legs, short bill, gray-brown on top

Name: Long-billed Dowitcher
Description: Medium-sized shorebird with very long bill, gray in winter, feeds in huge flocks, usually best left as dowitcher sp.

Name: Greater Yellowlegs
Description: Speckled gray plumage, long bill, bright yellow legs

Name: Willet
Description: The most generic shorebird, pretty big with medium, thick bill and gray plumage, but flashy wings when it flies

Name: Ring-billed Gull
Description: Rather small gull with yellow feet, petite bill with a dark ring

Name: California Gull
Description: Most common gull inland, medium size with yellow legs and dark mantle, saved the Mormons

Name: Glaucous-winged Gull
Description: Big gull, wingtips are the same gray color as the mantle, mates with Western (hybridity!)

Name: Double-crested Cormorant
Description: Large black cormorant with orange face and turqouise eyes (if you can see them)

Name: White-tailed Kite
Description: White raptor with red eyes and gray on top, hovers (all the time)

Name: Red-tailed Hawk
Description: RTHA - the classic hawk

Name: Belted Kingfisher
Description: Medium-sized blue and white bird, perches above streams and dives in for fish

Name: Northern Flicker
Description: A big woodpecker, gray and brown, spotted breast, flashy red tail and wings, loud calls

Name: Tree Swallow
Description: A very sleek swallow: shiny turquoise on top and clean white on the bottom (adult), the juvenile is nondescript and brown

Name: Bushtit
Description: Tiny gray birds that are impossible to count, tinkling calls

Name: Northern Mockingbird
Description: Master of mimicry, sings at night, gray bird with flashy wings in flight

Name: American Robin
Description: Red-orange breast, yellow bill, nice song

Name: House Finch
Description: Streaked gray-brown bird, males sometimes come in orange or yellow colors instead of red

Name: Fox Sparrow
Description: Dark rufous sparrow with a spotted breast, forages in thick vegetation

Name: White-crowned Sparrow
Description: Golden-crowned Sparrow but with a white crown

Name: Golden-crowned Sparrow
Description: White-crowned Sparrow but with a golden crow

Name: Song Sparrow
Description: Dark sparrow, streaked breast, "jimp" call, forages on the ground

Name: California Towhee
Description: Plain gray brown, orange vent, metallic call

Name: Common Yellowthroat
Description: Black mask and yellow throat, sings "whichity, whichity" in the marsh

Name: Canada Goose
Description: Everywhere on lawns, always

Name: Anna's Hummingbird
Description: If you listen, you hear them everywhere (because they are)

Name: American Coot
Description: Black wading bird with huge webbed yellow feet

Name: Great Egret
Description: Armaun! Very elegant egret (minus the call)

Name: Snowy Egret
Description: Miniature Great Egret, but thinner black bill and legs, cool plumes in breeding season

Name: Black-crowned Night-Heron
Description: Black back and cap, heavy bill, hunts on lawns at night

Name: Turkey Vulture
Description: TV

Name: Red-naped Sapsucker
Description: Armaun!!! Birding god

Name: Acorn Woodpecker
Description: Loud and raucous, stores acorns in trees, clown pattern on the face

Name: Nuttall's Woodpecker
Description: Stripey woodpecker, makes loud rattle calls

Name: Black Phoebe
Description: Flicks you off, but it's still a cool bird

Name: Ruby-crowned Kinglet
Description: Or Hutton's Vireo? Small, gray-green, yellow legs

Name: White-breasted Nuthatch
Description: Goes upside down on trees, funny calls

Name: Lesser Goldfinch
Description: A tiny bird with a triangle bill, black and yellow on the photo (gray irl)

Name: Yellow-rumped Warbler
Description: Butterbutt: small, gray with yellow sides and rump, everywhere in the winter
